   <titleInfo>
      <title>Interview with Hilary Hunter, 2017-03-15</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>Interview with Hilary Hunter, resident of Gatlinburg. Hunter recounts the surprising speed of the fire and the severity of the wind. She discusses her evacuation stay and the return to find her home intact. This is a representative quote from the interview: "Then I went acoss the street to my neighbors and told them we have to leave, panicking at this point."</abstract>
